<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO CLASS LASS</font><br>
<tt>Wed Oct  8 22:02:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Class Lass,<br><br>
Your points are articulate and well made, and I agree that my responses here appear somewhat uncharacteristic of my usual and customary approach to things. There are points that I have made, however, that are as valid. The POV, Point of View, philosophy of this site, is unchanged since it's inception.<br><br>
From where I sit, the tawdry exchange between myself and &quot;whoever&quot; was necessary to make several points that are interconnected with some exchanges elsewhere on this site. You can read a summary of some of my discontent above on my posting of &quot;Sat Oct 4 23:09:12&quot;, as well as my introductory remarks to the initiator of this thread.<br><br>
You need also to be aware that there are feelings associated with my points that also needed to be addressed. Anger and outrage come through clearly. The need for self preservation of my self esteem should also be evident. Although the exchange appears coarse, and perhaps beneath my dignity as Tom implied, it was necessary, and I have not the slightest regret about any of it.<br><br>
It is funny, but the issues have nothing to do with the Vietnam topic of this site. Respect for others, honorable dealings and fair play, genuine debate of differences, and dignity, are the real issues with which I have concern. <br><br>
I took a stand, defended my position, and stuck with it. As I said, I have no regrets, and would do the same thing all over again under the same circumstances.     
